@startuml ReportEase_Sequence_SoumettreReclamation
!theme plain
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F4F6F7
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #7F8C8D
skinparam ArrowColor #2C3E50
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #7F8C8D
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9E7
skinparam noteBorderColor #B7950B

title Diagramme de Sequence — Soumettre une reclamation (SPA + API REST)

actor       "Medecin"            as MED
participant "SPA\n(React)"       as SPA
participant "API REST\n(Django)" as API
database    "MongoDB"            as DB
actor       "AdminIT"            as IT

== 1. Consulter mes reclamations ==
MED -> SPA : 1. Acceder a la page "Reclamations"
SPA -> API : 2. GET /api/complaints/
API -> DB  : 3. Recherche {doctorId: user.id}
DB  --> API: 4. Liste des reclamations
API --> SPA: 5. 200 OK + liste
SPA --> MED: 6. Affiche l'historique

== 2. Soumettre une nouvelle reclamation ==
MED -> SPA : 7. Clique "Nouvelle reclamation"
MED -> SPA : 8. Saisit titre + description
SPA -> API : 9. POST /api/complaints/\n{title, description}

alt [Champs invalides]
  API --> SPA: 10a. 400 Bad Request
  SPA --> MED: 11a. "Titre et description requis"
else [Donnees valides]
  API -> DB  : 10b. Insert reclamation\n(status = "pending")
  DB  --> API: 11b. Document cree
  API --> SPA: 12b. 201 Created
  SPA --> MED: 13b. "Reclamation soumise"
end

== 3. Traitement par l'AdminIT ==
IT  -> SPA : 14. Consulte la liste + repond
SPA -> API : 15. PUT /api/complaints/{id}\n{status, response}
API -> DB  : 16. Met a jour la reclamation
API --> SPA: 17. 200 OK
SPA --> IT : 18. "Reclamation mise a jour"

note right of API
  Toutes les requetes incluent
  l'en-tete Authorization:
  Bearer <access_token>.
  Roles autorises :
  - POST  : doctor, admin
  - GET   : doctor, admin, adminIT
  - PUT   : adminIT uniquement
end note

@enduml
